long proceedings myung hwan yu a former korean minister of foreign affairs and trade and a 2010 2011 stanford ksp visiting scholar presented the conference public keynote address the north korean nuclear program and inter korean relations on the evening of february 24 stanford ksp welcomed one hundred and twenty guests including stanford faculty and students and program supporters from the san francisco bay area and worldwide to a dinner to honor its long time supporters the anniversary celebration concluded the next day as conference participants and other invited guests took part in special outings around the bay area commemorating the events twenty reporters from major korean language media entities participated in the three days of anniversary activities covering the events online and through print publications and television stanford ksp invites you to explore a wealth of selected media coverage event descriptions the tenth anniversary commemorative booklet related background information and images media coverage stanford daily yu urges end to north korean nuclear program stanford magazine korean studies program marks ten years hankyoreh tenth anniversary of the korean studies program at stanford university in korean joong ang daily dprk 2012 seminar held at stanford university's shorenstein aparc to commemorate the tenth anniversary of its korean studies program in korean yonhap news tenth anniversary of the korean studies program at stanford university in korean yonhap news ten years of the korean studies program at stanford university in korean event descriptions challenges and opportunities in northeast asia koret conference dprk 2012 the north korean nuclear program and inter korean relations commemorative booklet ten years of korean studies at stanford related information celebrating ten years of korean studies at stanford images simpleviewer requires macromedia flash get macromedia flash if you have flash installed click to view gallery large gallery cel